#pull in function to calculate model estimates and standard errors
source(here::here("analysis_code","extract_coefficients_function.R"))

Pull dissimilarity table

#Pull Dissimilarity Means
jaccard_index_allyears <- readRDS(here::here("output","jaccard_index_VEGAN", "jaccard_index_allyears.rds"))

#make survey and survey unit factors
jaccard_index_allyears[,survey:=factor(survey)][,survey_unit:=factor(survey_unit)]

#adjust years
jaccard_index_allyears[,year_adj := year-min(year)+1]

#add new variable for year in sequence per region
jaccard_index_allyears[,first_year := min(year),.(survey_unit)]
jaccard_index_allyears[,last_year := max(year),.(survey_unit)]

#jaccard_index_allyears[,year_in_seq := year-first_year+1]

jaccard_index_allyears[,years_sampled := last_year-first_year+1]

List of surveys

#list of surveys
survey_unit.list <- levels(factor(jaccard_index_allyears$survey_unit))

Pull in palette and name helper

source(here::here("analysis_code","color_links.R"))

##Make GAM (Generalized Additive Models)

Jaccard

jaccard_total_gam <- gam(annual_dissimilarity_value ~ year + s(survey_unit, year, bs = "fs", m = 1),#random smooth
                            data = jaccard_index_allyears[dissimilarity_metric == "jaccard_dissimilarity_index_binary"])

Jaccard for abundance

jaccard_abundance_gam <- gam(annual_dissimilarity_value ~ year + s(survey_unit, year, bs = "fs", m = 1),#random smooth
                            data = jaccard_index_allyears[dissimilarity_metric == "jaccard_dissimilarity_index_abundance"])

Jaccard for relative abundance

jaccard_abundance_relative_gam <- gam(annual_dissimilarity_value ~ year + s(survey_unit, year, bs = "fs", m = 1),#random smooth
                            data = jaccard_index_allyears[dissimilarity_metric == "jaccard_dissimilarity_index_relative_abundance"])

##Make linear mixed effect models (allow random dissimilarity vs time slope for survey unit)

These all converged

#running with lme instead of lmer gave same results, but allowed for calculation of p-value

#Jaccard total with lme
jaccard_total_lme <- lme(annual_dissimilarity_value ~ year_adj, random = (~1 + year_adj|survey_unit),data = jaccard_index_allyears[dissimilarity_metric == "jaccard_dissimilarity_index_binary"])

#Jaccard total with lmer
jaccard_total_lmer <- lmer(annual_dissimilarity_value ~ year_adj + (1 + year_adj|survey_unit),data = jaccard_index_allyears[dissimilarity_metric == "jaccard_dissimilarity_index_binary"])

summary(jaccard_total_lme)
Linear mixed-effects model fit by REML
  Data: jaccard_index_allyears[dissimilarity_metric == "jaccard_dissimilarity_index_binary"]

anova(jaccard_total_lme)

#EXPORT JACCARD COEFFICIENTS
jaccard_total_coefs <- data.table(coef(jaccard_total_lme))
jaccard_total_coefs[,survey_unit := rownames(coef(jaccard_total_lme))][,Year := round(year_adj,5)][,Intercept := round(`(Intercept)`,2)]
#View(jaccard_total_coefs)

jaccard_total_coefs <- jaccard_total_coefs[color_link, on = "survey_unit"]

jaccard_total_coefs.exp <- jaccard_total_coefs[,.(Survey_Name_Season, Intercept, Year)]

#export this table
fwrite(jaccard_total_coefs.exp, file = here::here("output","jaccard_total_coefs.exp.csv"))

##Linear Model

Also, build a simple linear model with an interaction (instead of random slope and intercept for survey) THIS IS HOW WE CLASSIFY SURVEYS as of fall 2023 (update from before, where we classified surveys from LMER) (Especially good because lmer didnât converge)

AICc(jaccard_total_gls)-AICc(jaccard_total_lm) #615.1913

[1] 615.1913
```r

#traditional linear model
jaccard_abundance_lm <- lm(annual_dissimilarity_value ~ year * survey_unit,data = jaccard_index_allyears[dissimilarity_metric == \jaccard_dissimilarity_index_abundance\])

#Use linear algebra to calculate coefficients and standard errors
jaccard_abundance_total_coefs.r <- data.table(lm_interaction_coefficients_se(jaccard_abundance_lm))

#Add survey names
jaccard_abundance_total_coefs.r[,survey_unit := sort(unique(jaccard_index_allyears[dissimilarity_metric == \jaccard_dissimilarity_index_abundance\,survey_unit]))]
  
  #homogenizing vs differentiating
  jaccard_abundance_total_coefs.r[,differentiating := ifelse((se< abs(estimate) & estimate > 0),1,0)][,homogenizing := ifelse((se< abs(estimate) & estimate < 0),1,0)]
  
  #lower and upper CI
    jaccard_abundance_total_coefs.r[,lwr := estimate-se][,upr:= estimate + se]
    
    #save as output
    fwrite(jaccard_abundance_total_coefs.r, here::here(\output\,\jaccard_abundance_total_coefs.r.csv\))
  
  jaccard_abundance_total_coefs_sum <- data.table(differentiating = sum(  jaccard_abundance_total_coefs.r$differentiating), homogenizing = sum(  jaccard_abundance_total_coefs.r$homogenizing))
  
  #hex by trend
  jaccard_abundance_total_coefs.r[,trend_color_jaccard_abundance := ifelse(homogenizing == 1,\#FFC109\, ifelse(differentiating == 1,\#D81C60\,\#1E88E5\))]
  
  #link to color link
  jaccard_abundance_total_coefs.r <- color_link[jaccard_abundance_total_coefs.r, on = \survey_unit\]
  
  #delete rows of surveys without abundance data
    jaccard_abundance_total_coefs.r <-     jaccard_abundance_total_coefs.r[complete.cases(  jaccard_abundance_total_coefs.r),]
  
  color_link_trend_jaccard_abundance <- jaccard_abundance_total_coefs.r[,.(survey_unit,Survey_Name_Season, hex,  trend_color_jaccard_abundance)]

jaccard_total_coefs.r[,Directional_Change_sig := ifelse(differentiating > 0, \Differentiation\,ifelse(homogenizing > 0 , \Homogenization\, \No Î²-diversity trend\))]
years_sampled <- unique(jaccard_index_allyears[,.(survey_unit, years_sampled)])
jaccard_total_coefs.r <- years_sampled[jaccard_total_coefs.r, on = \survey_unit\]

(jaccard_total_Dissimilarity_Coef_errorbar_reduced_colorbytrend_LINEAR_MODEL <- ggplot(data = jaccard_total_coefs.r, aes(x = reorder(Survey_Name_Season, estimate) , y = estimate), label = Survey_Name_Season) +
    geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = lwr, ymax = upr), fill = \grey\, width = 0) + #add confidence intervals
  geom_point(aes(size = years_sampled, color = Directional_Change_sig), stat = 'identity') +
  scale_color_manual(values = c(\#D81C60\,\#FFC109\,\#1E88E5\), name = \Î²-diversity trend\n(Jaccard dissimilarity)\, guide=\none\) +
  scale_size_binned(range = c(1,8), name = \Survey period length\n(years)\) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0) +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(-0.0075, 0.0075, by = 0.0025), labels = c(\-0.0075\,\\,\-0.0025\,\0\, \0.0025\, \\,  \\)) +
  xlab(\Survey unit\) +
  ylab(\Î²-diversity trend\n(Jaccard dissimilarity)\) + #total jaccard dissimilarity trend
  coord_flip() +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(axis.text.y = element_text(face = \bold\), axis.title.y = element_blank(), axis.text.x = element_text(size = 15), axis.title.x = element_text(size = 15), legend.position = c(0.3,0.8), legend.direction = \vertical\, legend.text = element_text(size = 15), legend.title = element_text(size = 16)))

###############
#FOR LINEAR MODEL INSTEAD OF LINEAR MIXED EFFECTS as of fall 2023
###############

jaccard_abundance_total_coefs.r[,Directional_Change_sig := ifelse(differentiating > 0, \Differentiation\,ifelse(homogenizing > 0 , \Homogenization\, \No Î²-diversity trend\))]
years_sampled <- unique(jaccard_index_allyears[,.(survey_unit, years_sampled)])
jaccard_abundance_total_coefs.r <- years_sampled[jaccard_abundance_total_coefs.r, on = \survey_unit\]

(Jaccard_abundance_Dissimilarity_Coef_errorbar_reduced_colorbytrend_LINEAR_MODEL <- ggplot(data = jaccard_abundance_total_coefs.r, aes(x = reorder(Survey_Name_Season, estimate) , y = estimate), label = Survey_Name_Season) +
    geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = lwr, ymax = upr), fill = \grey\, width = 0) + #add confidence intervals
  geom_point(aes(size = years_sampled, color = Directional_Change_sig), stat = 'identity') +
  scale_color_manual(values = c(\#D81C60\,\#FFC109\,\#1E88E5\), name = \Dissimilarity trend\, guide=\none\) +
  scale_size_binned(range = c(1,8), name = \Survey period length\n(years)\) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0) +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(-0.01, 0.005, by = 0.0025), labels = c(\-0.0010\,\\,\-0.0050\,\\,\0\, \0.0025\,\0.0050\)) +
  xlab(\Survey unit\) +
  ylab(\Î²-diversity trend\) + 
  coord_flip() +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(axis.text.y = element_text(face = \bold\), axis.title.y = element_blank(), axis.text.x = element_text(size = 15), axis.title.x = element_text(size = 15), legend.position = c(0.3,0.8), legend.direction = \vertical\, legend.text = element_text(size = 15), legend.title = element_text(size = 16), plot.margin = margin(5,20,5,5,unit = \pt\)))

```r

jaccard_relative_abundance_total_coefs.r[,Directional_Change_sig := ifelse(differentiating > 0, \Differentiation\,ifelse(homogenizing > 0 , \Homogenization\, \No Î²-diversity trend\))]
years_sampled <- unique(jaccard_index_allyears[,.(survey_unit, years_sampled)])
jaccard_relative_abundance_total_coefs.r <- years_sampled[jaccard_relative_abundance_total_coefs.r, on = \survey_unit\]

(Jaccard_relative_abundance_Dissimilarity_Coef_errorbar_reduced_colorbytrend_LINEAR_MODEL <- ggplot(data = jaccard_relative_abundance_total_coefs.r, aes(x = reorder(Survey_Name_Season, estimate) , y = estimate), label = Survey_Name_Season) +
    geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = lwr, ymax = upr), fill = \grey\, width = 0) + #add confidence intervals
  geom_point(aes(size = years_sampled, color = Directional_Change_sig), stat = 'identity') +
  scale_color_manual(values = c(\#D81C60\,\#FFC109\,\#1E88E5\), name = \Dissimilarity trend\, guide=\none\) +
  scale_size_binned(range = c(1,8), name = \Survey period length\n(years)\) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0) +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(-0.01, 0.005, by = 0.0025), labels = c(\-0.0010\,\\,\-0.0050\,\\,\0\, \0.0025\,\0.0050\)) +
  xlab(\Survey unit\) +
  ylab(\Î²-diversity trend\) + #total BC dissimilarity trend
  coord_flip() +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(axis.text.y = element_text(face = \bold\), axis.title.y = element_blank(), axis.text.x = element_text(size = 15), axis.title.x = element_text(size = 15), legend.position = c(0.3,0.8), legend.direction = \vertical\, legend.text = element_text(size = 15), legend.title = element_text(size = 16), plot.margin = margin(5,20,5,5,unit = \pt\)))

```r
jaccard_total_coefs.r[,jaccard_coefficient := estimate][,Directional_Change_sig_jaccard := Directional_Change_sig]
all_total_coefs <- jaccard_total_coefs.r[,.(survey_unit, Survey_Name_Season, jaccard_coefficient, Directional_Change_sig_jaccard, trend_color_jaccard)]

#add jaccard abundance metrics
jaccard_abundance_total_coefs.r[,jaccard_abundance_coefficient := estimate][,Directional_Change_sig_jaccard_abundance := Directional_Change_sig]
jaccard_abundance_total_coefs.r.r <- jaccard_abundance_total_coefs.r[,.(survey_unit, jaccard_abundance_coefficient, Directional_Change_sig_jaccard_abundance, trend_color_jaccard_abundance)]
all_total_coefs <- all_total_coefs[jaccard_abundance_total_coefs.r.r, on = \survey_unit\]

#add relative jaccard abundance metrics
jaccard_relative_abundance_total_coefs.r[,jaccard_abundance_relative_coefficient := estimate][,Directional_Change_sig_jaccard_abundance_relative := Directional_Change_sig]
jaccard_relative_abundance_total_coefs.r.r <- jaccard_relative_abundance_total_coefs.r[,.(survey_unit, jaccard_abundance_relative_coefficient, Directional_Change_sig_jaccard_abundance_relative, trend_color_jaccard_relative_abundance)]
all_total_coefs <- all_total_coefs[jaccard_relative_abundance_total_coefs.r.r, on = \survey_unit\]

#plot
(Dissimilarity_Coef_errorbar_reduced_colorbytrend_LINEAR_MODEL_comparison <- ggplot(data = all_total_coefs, aes(x = reorder(Survey_Name_Season, jaccard_coefficient)), label = Survey_Name_Season) +
  geom_point(aes(y = jaccard_coefficient, fill = Directional_Change_sig_jaccard), stat = 'identity',shape = 21, color = \black\, size = 5) +
  geom_point(aes(y = jaccard_abundance_coefficient, color = Directional_Change_sig_jaccard_abundance), stat = 'identity', shape = 15, alpha = 0.5,size = 5) +
  geom_point(aes(y = jaccard_abundance_relative_coefficient, color = Directional_Change_sig_jaccard_abundance_relative), stat = 'identity', shape = 17, alpha = 0.5,size = 5) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c(\#D81C60\,\#FFC109\,\#1E88E5\), name = \Î²-diversity trend\, guide=\none\) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c(\#D81C60\,\#FFC109\,\#1E88E5\), name = \Î²-diversity trend\, guide=\none\) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0) +
 # scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(-0.0075, 0.0075, by = 0.0025), labels = c(\-0.0075\,\\,\-0.0025\,\0\, \0.0025\, \\,  \\)) +
  xlab(\Survey unit\) +
  ylab(\Î²-diversity trend\) + #total jaccard dissimilarity trend
  coord_flip() +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(axis.text.y = element_text(face = \bold\), axis.title.y = element_blank(), axis.text.x = element_text(size = 15), axis.title.x = element_text(size = 15), legend.position = c(0.3,0.8), legend.direction = \vertical\, legend.text = element_text(size = 15), legend.title = element_text(size = 16)))

ggsave(Dissimilarity_Coef_errorbar_reduced_colorbytrend_LINEAR_MODEL_comparison, 
       path = here::here(\figures\), filename = \Dissimilarity_Coef_errorbar_reduced_colorbytrend_LINEAR_MODEL_comparison.jpg\, height = 7, width = 7)

```r
```r
#generate list again, as for some reason it doesn't stay in environment
survey_unit.list <- levels(factor(jaccard_index_allyears$survey_unit))

#generate new data to smooth lines (need year and season survey combinations)
year_survey_unit_expand.dt <- data.table(survey_unit = as.character(NULL), year = as.numeric(NULL), year_adj = as.numeric(NULL ))

for (i in 1:length(survey_unit.list)) {
  #generate year vectors
  survey_unit_years <- unique(jaccard_index_allyears[survey_unit == survey_unit.list[i],.(survey_unit, year, year_adj)])
  
  years <- seq(min(survey_unit_years[,year]), max(survey_unit_years[,year]), by = 0.1)
  
  year_adjust <- seq(min(survey_unit_years[,year_adj]), max(survey_unit_years[,year_adj]), by = 0.1)
  
  year_survey_unit_expand.dt_addition <- data.table(survey_unit = survey_unit.list[i], year = years, year_adj = year_adjust)
  
  year_survey_unit_expand.dt <- rbind(year_survey_unit_expand.dt, year_survey_unit_expand.dt_addition)
}


#add colors and names to full year and survey unit combination table
year_survey_unit_expand_jaccard.dt <- year_survey_unit_expand.dt[color_link_trend_jaccard, on = \survey_unit\]

setorder(trend_colors_jaccard.dt, survey_unit)


points_wavylines_jaccard_total_year_reduced_gam_colorbytrend <- ggplot() +
  #full LMER predictions (black)
  geom_ribbon(data = lmer_jaccard_total_predictions, aes(x = year, ymin = jaccard_lmer_preds_lowerCI, ymax = jaccard_lmer_preds_upperCI), fill = \grey\, alpha = 0.3) +
    geom_line(data = lmer_jaccard_total_predictions, aes(x = year, y = jaccard_lmer_preds), color = \black\) +
  #points by trend
  geom_point(data = jaccard_index_allyears[dissimilarity_metric ==\jaccard_dissimilarity_index_binary\], cols = \year_adj\,
             aes(x = year,
                 y = annual_dissimilarity_value,
                 fill = survey_unit), alpha = 0.4, size = 1, shape = 21, color = \white\) +
  #squiggly lines by survey unit based GAM and colored by trend
    geom_line(data = year_survey_unit_expand_jaccard.dt, cols = \year_adj\,
             aes(x = year,
                 y = jaccard_glm_mod_fit,
                 color = survey_unit), alpha = 0.6) +
  #confidence intervals for individual GAM
  geom_ribbon(data = year_survey_unit_expand_jaccard.dt, cols = \year_adj\, 
              aes(x = year, ymin=jaccard_glm_mod_fit-jaccard_glm_mod_fit_SE, ymax=jaccard_glm_mod_fit+jaccard_glm_mod_fit_SE, fill =  survey_unit), alpha=0.1) + #add standard error
  #set color by survey
    scale_color_manual(values = trend_colors_jaccard.dt$trend_color, name = \Survey Unit\) +
  scale_fill_manual(values =trend_colors_jaccard.dt$trend_color, guide = \none\) +
  theme_classic() +
  lims(x = c(min(jaccard_index_allyears[dissimilarity_metric == \jaccard_dissimilarity_index_binary\,year]),max(jaccard_index_allyears[dissimilarity_metric == \jaccard_dissimilarity_index_binary\,year]))
       ) +
  xlab(\Year\n\) +
ylab(\Î²-diversity\n(Jaccard dissimilarity)\) +
  theme(legend.position = \null\, axis.text = element_text(size = 15), axis.title = element_text(size = 15))

    draw_plot(points_wavylines_jaccard_total_year_reduced_gam_colorbytrend + theme(axis.text = element_text(size = 14)),
                                         x = 1, y = 1, width = 20, height = 20) +
    draw_plot(jaccard_total_Dissimilarity_Coef_errorbar_reduced_colorbytrend_LINEAR_MODEL +
        theme(legend.key.size = unit(0.5, 'cm'), #change legend key size
              axis.text = element_text(size = 8)), #change legend text font size),
                                         x = 20, y = 1, width = 19, height = 20) +
    draw_plot(get_legend(directional_change_legend_plot_colorbytrend + 
      theme(legend.key.size = unit(0.5, 'cm'), #change legend key size
        legend.title = element_text(size=16), #change legend title font size
        legend.text = element_text(size=15))), #change legend text font size)
                                x = 26, y = 8, width = 3, height = 2) +
  geom_text(aes(x = 2, y = 20.7), label = (\a.\), size =8, fontface = \bold\) +
  geom_text(aes(x =20, y = 20.7), label = (\b.\), size =8, fontface = \bold\)

#list of surveys
survey_unit.list_jaccard <- levels(factor(jaccard_index_allyears_jaccard$survey_unit))

# Function to compare GAM and linear model fits
compare_models <- function(subset_data) {
  # Fit GAM model with \fs\ basis and single smooth term
  gam_model <- gam(annual_dissimilarity_value ~ s(year, bs = \fs\, m = 1), data = subset_data)
  
  # Fit linear model
  lm_model <- lm(annual_dissimilarity_value ~ year, data = subset_data)
  
  # Calculate AICc values
  aicc_gam <- AICc(gam_model)
  aicc_lm <- AICc(lm_model)
  
  #Calculate p-values
  gam_pvalue <- summary(gam_model)$s.table[1,4]
  lm_pvalue <- summary(lm_model)$coefficients[2,4]
  
  comparison <- ifelse((abs(aicc_gam-aicc_lm) < 2 | (aicc_gam == aicc_lm)),\Same\,
                       ifelse(((abs(aicc_gam-aicc_lm) > 2 & (aicc_gam < aicc_lm))),\GAM\,
                              ifelse(((abs(aicc_gam-aicc_lm) > 2 & (aicc_gam > aicc_lm))), \Linear\,NA)))
  
   return(data.table(Survey = unique(subset_data$Survey_Name_Season)[1],
                     survey_unit = unique(subset_data$survey_unit),
                    comparison = comparison,
                    aicc_gam = aicc_gam,
                    gam_p = gam_pvalue,
                    aicc_lm = aicc_lm,
                    lm_p = lm_pvalue))
}


############## Compare models for each survey name and bind the results
GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total <- data.table()

for (i in 1:length(survey_unit.list_jaccard)) {
  GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total_single <- compare_models(jaccard_index_allyears_jaccard[survey_unit == survey_unit.list_jaccard[i],])
  GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total <- rbind(GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total, GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total_single)
}

GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total

#round to 2 significant figures

#names of numeric columns
numeric_cols <- names(GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total)[sapply(GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total, is.numeric)]

# Apply signif() only to numeric columns
GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total[, (numeric_cols) := lapply(.SD, function(x) if (is.numeric(x)) signif(x, digits = 3) else x), .SDcols = numeric_cols]

GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total.f <- GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total[,-2]

colnames(GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total.f) <- c(\Survey\,\Model comparison\, \GAM AICc\,\GAM p-value\,\LM AICc\, \LM p-value\)

fwrite(GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total.f, here::here(\output\,\GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total.csv\))


##################generate predicted GAM values
GAM_outputs <- function(subset.data) {
# Fit GAM model with \fs\ basis and single smooth term
  gam_model <- gam(annual_dissimilarity_value ~ s(year, bs = \fs\, m = 1), data = subset.data)
  
  pred_values <- predict(gam_model, se.fit = T)
  pred_table <- data.table(year = subset.data$year, predicted_dissimilarity = as.numeric(pred_values$fit), predicted_lwr = as.numeric(pred_values$fit)-as.numeric(pred_values$se.fit), predicted_upr = as.numeric(pred_values$fit)+as.numeric(pred_values$se.fit))
  
  st_dev_pred_dissim <- sd(pred_table$predicted_dissimilarity)
  return(signif(st_dev_pred_dissim,2))
}

predicted_values_jaccard <- data.table(survey_unit = survey_unit.list_jaccard, SD_pred_dissim = as.numeric())

for (i in 1:length(survey_unit.list_jaccard)) {
  st_dev_pred_dissim <- GAM_outputs(jaccard_index_allyears_jaccard[survey_unit == survey_unit.list_jaccard[i]])
  predicted_values_jaccard[i,\SD_pred_dissim\] <- st_dev_pred_dissim
}

#merge witih GAM vs LM

GAM_lm_SD_jaccard_total <- predicted_values_jaccard[GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total, on = \survey_unit\]

GAM_lm_SD_jaccard_total.f <- GAM_lm_SD_jaccard_total[,.(Survey, SD_pred_dissim, aicc_gam, gam_p, aicc_lm, lm_p, comparison)]

colnames(GAM_lm_SD_jaccard_total.f) <- c(\Survey\,\SD over time of predicted GAM values\, \GAM AICc\,\GAM p-value\,\LM AICc\, \LM p-value\,\Model comparison\)

View(GAM_lm_SD_jaccard_total.f)

fwrite(GAM_lm_SD_jaccard_total.f, here::here(\output\,\GAM_lm_SD_jaccard_total.f.csv\))

```r
#plot each independently for supplement
#all survey names = 
all_survey_names <- color_link_trend_jaccard$survey_unit

#set order of levels of Survey Name Season by survey unit
jaccard_index_allyears_jaccard[,Survey_Name_Season := factor(Survey_Name_Season, levels = trend_colors_jaccard.dt$Survey_Name_Season, ordered = T)]

#change year to integer
jaccard_index_allyears_jaccard[,year:=as.integer(year)]

#split into 2 and use facet
#first 17
points_wavylines_jaccard_total_year_reduced_gam_colorbytrend_individual_facet_1_20 <- ggplot() +
  geom_point(data = jaccard_index_allyears_jaccard[survey_unit  %in% all_survey_names[c(1:20)]],
             aes(x = as.integer(year),
                 y = annual_dissimilarity_value), alpha = 0.3) +

    geom_smooth(data = jaccard_index_allyears_jaccard[survey_unit  %in% all_survey_names[c(1:20)]],
             aes(x = as.integer(year),
                 y = annual_dissimilarity_value,
                 color = survey_unit,
                 fill = survey_unit), method = \lm\, linewidth = 0.5) +
  geom_smooth(data = jaccard_index_allyears_jaccard[survey_unit %in% all_survey_names[c(1:20)]],
              aes(x = as.integer(year),
                  y = annual_dissimilarity_value), method = \gam\, linewidth = 0.5, formula = y ~ s(x, bs = \fs\, m = 1), color = \black\) +
    scale_color_manual(values =    color_link_trend_jaccard$trend_color[1:20], name = \Survey Unit\) +
    scale_fill_manual(values =    color_link_trend_jaccard$trend_color[1:20], name = \Survey Unit\) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = ~ axisTicks(., log = FALSE)) +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(size = 7)) +
  xlab(\Year\) +
ylab(\Î²-diversity\n(Jaccard dissimilarity)\) +
  facet_wrap(~Survey_Name_Season, ncol = 4, scales = \free\) +
  theme(axis.text = element_text(size = 8), axis.title = element_text(size = 12), legend.position = \null\)

ggsave(points_wavylines_jaccard_total_year_reduced_gam_colorbytrend_individual_facet_1_20, path =  here::here(\figures\), filename = \points_wavylines_jaccard_total_year_reduced_gam_colorbytrend_individual_facet_1_20.png\, height = 12, width = 9.5)

#second portion
points_wavylines_jaccard_total_year_reduced_gam_colorbytrend_individual_facet_21_34 <- ggplot() +
  geom_point(data = jaccard_index_allyears_jaccard[survey_unit  %in% all_survey_names[c(21:34)]],
             aes(x = as.integer(year),
                 y = annual_dissimilarity_value), alpha = 0.3) +

    geom_smooth(data = jaccard_index_allyears_jaccard[survey_unit  %in% all_survey_names[c(21:34)]],
             aes(x = as.integer(year),
                 y = annual_dissimilarity_value,
                 color = survey_unit,
                 fill = survey_unit), method = \lm\, linewidth = 0.5) +
  geom_smooth(data = jaccard_index_allyears_jaccard[survey_unit %in% all_survey_names[c(21:34)]],
              aes(x = as.integer(year),
                  y = annual_dissimilarity_value), method = \gam\, linewidth = 0.5, formula = y ~ s(x, bs = \fs\, m = 1), color = \black\) +
    scale_color_manual(values =    color_link_trend_jaccard$trend_color[21:34], name = \Survey Unit\) +
    scale_fill_manual(values =    color_link_trend_jaccard$trend_color[21:34], name = \Survey Unit\) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = ~ axisTicks(., log = FALSE)) +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(size = 7)) +
  xlab(\Year\) +
ylab(\Î²-diversity\n(Jaccard dissimilarity)\) +
  facet_wrap(~Survey_Name_Season, ncol = 4, scales = \free\) +
  theme(axis.text = element_text(size = 8), axis.title = element_text(size = 12), legend.position = \null\)

ggsave(points_wavylines_jaccard_total_year_reduced_gam_colorbytrend_individual_facet_21_34, path =  here::here(\figures\), filename = \points_wavylines_jaccard_total_year_reduced_gam_colorbytrend_individual_facet_21_34.png\, height = 10, width = 9.5)
